    Class Description
    AddOrUpdate
    This ENUM is used for switch statements to load add or update forms.
    AddUpdate
    This class holds the ADD or UPDATE status.
    AlertTracker
    This class lets the other controllers know if the 15 minute appointment alert has been triggered.
    AppointmentAlert
    This ENUM is used for the 15 minute Appointment Alert switch statements.
    AppointmentController
    This class controls the Appointment Form.
    AppointmentsAccess
    This class is used to interact with the Appointments table in the MySQL database.
    AppointmentsObj
    Creates Appointment objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    ContactsAccess
    This class is used to interact with the contact table in the MySQL database.
    ContactsObj
    Creates Contact objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    CountriesAccess
    This class is used to interact with the countries table in the MySQL database.
    CountriesObj
    Creates Country objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    CustomerController
    This class controls the Customer Form.
    CustomersAccess
    This class is used to interact with the customers table in the MySQL database.
    CustomersObj
    Creates Customer objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    DatabaseConnection
    This class connects to the database using my assigned login details.
    DatabaseQuery
    This class stores and retrieves SQL statements for methods in other classes to access the database.
    FirstLevelAccess
    This class is used to interact with the first_level_divisions table in the MySQL database.
    FirstLevelObj
    Creates FirstLevel (first level division) objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    HomeController
    This class controls the Customer Form.
    LoginController
    This class controls the login page.
    Main
    The program starts with this class.
    UsersAccess
    This class is used to interact with the users table in the MySQL database and verify user login credentials.
    UsersObj
    Creates User objects and provides methods to access attributes of the object.
    UtilityMessage
    This interface is used for reducing the need to write extra String values in some methods of controller classes.
